<h2>What is this?</h2>
<p>Snippet Monkey <%= image_tag "favicon.ico"%> is a Ruby on Rails based web application <strong>developed for "developers"</strong>. This application can be used by developers for storing the <strong> URLs of blogs or snippets from blogs</strong> for future development use.</p>

<p>Snippet was created by <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/kannancet">Snippet Team</a>. The source is available as open-source in Github <%= link_to "here", "https://github.com/kannancet"%>.</p>

<p>You might have come across situations where you resolve some bug using some snippet or blog and encounters the same bug after a few months. Unfortunately you are on a different development machine and you are unable to find the resource by searching it on web again. Snippet Monkey <%= image_tag "favicon.ico"%> comes handy in such situations. Just save your resource URL or Snippet into this portal with a heading tag. Any its webified for ever to be accessed from anywhere and any time.</p>
